performance, where he saves an injured aerialist, Lorelei (Jessica Brown Findlay), aided
by a nameless hunchback (Daniel Radcliffe) enslaved by the circus' ringleader, and who
harbors feelings for the girl. Impressed by the hunchback's vast knowledge of human
anatomy, acquired from stolen books, Victor rescues him, drains the cyst on his back that
causes his physical abnormality and develops a harness to improve his posture, and then
names him "Igor" after a recently deceased roommate. The two then become partners in
Victor's ongoing experiments to create life through artificial means, incurring the wrath
of religious police inspector Roderick Turpin (Andrew Scott), who views their experiments
as sinful.
